From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ken Cunningham <kencu@macports.org>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 17:30:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] install_megadrivers: stop stripping aliases at extensionless
 names

When --libname-suffix is dylib but the DRI driver alias is still named
*.so, the alias-generation loop never reaches .dylib.  For example:

  driver = swrast_dri.so
  libname_suffix = dylib

The first iteration creates:

  swrast_dri -> swrast_dri.so

Then splitext('swrast_dri') returns ('swrast_dri', ''), so the loop
continues forever, repeatedly unlinking and recreating the same symlink.

Stop when there is no extension left.  This preserves the existing
progressive alias creation for names with versioned suffixes, while
avoiding an infinite loop for extensionless names.
---
 bin/install_megadrivers.py | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/bin/install_megadrivers.py b/bin/install_megadrivers.py
index 00000000000..00000000000 100755
--- a/bin/install_megadrivers.py
+++ b/bin/install_megadrivers.py
@@ -79,7 +79,7 @@ def main():
             os.chdir(to)
 
             name, ext = os.path.splitext(driver)
-            while ext != '.' + args.libname_suffix:
+            while ext and ext != '.' + args.libname_suffix:
                 if os.path.lexists(name):
                     os.unlink(name)
                 os.symlink(driver, name)
-- 
